<paragraph blockId="89.[189,1399,1229,1365]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
FRUIT. Elliptical, accrescent at the apex and forming an inflated cap (representing about half of the length). Epicarp pilose, with yellow long and thin hair. Mesocarp ca 
<quantity box="[1026,1121,1265,1292]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="100.0">100 µm</quantity>
thick when dry. Calyx persistent, separated from the fruit by a short gynophore. Length 
<quantity box="[991,1125,1302,1329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="41.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="33.0">33–50 mm</quantity>
, width 11.2–26.0 mm, thickness 8.6–12.0 mm.
</paragraph>
